{
  "texts": [
    "CORAL demonstrates stable performance as output resolution increases, while OFormer struggles significantly when queried on unseen grids for both datasets.",
    "ENMA and AROMA show similar trends as the super-resolution difficulty increases; however, AROMA's performance degrades more rapidly with lower input grid densities.",
    "Overall, ENMA's auto-encoder proves to be the most robust, both to variations in input sparsity and to changes in query resolution.",
